race.comment: SECRET INTENT (2) disappointed last start when a long way off them at Bunbury but her prior form stands out in this race. She was only beaten narrowly at Pinjarra and Belmont before the spell. Easier here and she lines up for the local barn. Can resume on a winning note. WRITTEN SIN (5) only missed by 1.9L at this track last time out when stretching out to the mile once more. Back to 1400m today is the query, though she shouldn't be too far away from the inside barrier. Can feature in the finish if she runs up to recent efforts. IMPORT (1) was very impressive on debut when flying home from the tail of the field to be 0.6L away in a blanket finish. Wheatley replaces the apprentice hoop now and the rise in trip should suit. Better for that effort and can get the job done this time. DESERT MADAME (6) can resume on a positive not for the new stable. GOLDEN OPERA (11) can bounce back following a disappointing effort most recently.
